{
  "text": "Next, we examined whether Foxg1 can regulate Tbr1 transcription by searching for Foxg1 consensus binding sites [CITATION_1] within 10 kb of the transcription start site of the Tbr1 gene (Fig. 4I ) . We identified a 4 kb region of the mouse Tbr1 promoter that consists of multiple conserved Foxg1 binding sequences (Fig. 4I ), which were cloned upstream of the luciferase reporter gene to assess transcription. Cotransfection of pCAGGS-Foxg1 reduced the luciferase reporter activity in Neuro2a cells by 31.0 Ϯ 2.9% ( p Ͻ 0.01; Fig. 4J ). These results indicated that Foxg1 can repress Tbr1 promoter activity in vitro.",
